==German==

===Etymology===
From {{prefix|n|immer|lang=de}}

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|/ˈnɪmɐ/|lang=de}}

===Adverb===
{{head|de|adverb}}

# [[no more]], [[no longer]]
# [[never more]], [[never again]]
# {{context|colloquial|regional|southern Germany|Austria|lang=de}} [[never]]

====Usage notes====
In northern Germany and many parts of central Germany, the word is used chiefly in some set phrases such as {{term|nie und nimmer||not by any means|lang=de}}. Otherwise it has an archaic or poetic ring to it. It is used more readily in southern Germany and Austria. In these areas it can even mean “never” (sense 3), which is not part of the general standard language and unlikely to be understood in the north.

